.\" ###### Setup ############################################################
.Dd March 17, 2026
.Dt Make-Clothify 1
.Os Make-Clothify
.\" ###### Name #############################################################
.Sh NAME
.Nm Make-Clothify
.Nd applies the GIMP "Clothify" effect on an image
.\" ###### Synopsis #########################################################
.\" Manpage syntax help:
.\" https://forums.freebsd.org/threads/howto-create-a-manpage-from-scratch.13200/
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm Make-Clothify
input_filename
output_filename
.br
.Op Fl d Ar depth | Fl Fl depth Ar depth
.br
.Op Fl q | Fl Fl quiet
.Op Fl w | Fl Fl verbose
.Nm Make-Clothify
.Op Fl h | Fl Fl help
.\" ###### Description ######################################################
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm Make-Clothify
runs GIMP to load an image, apply the "Clothify" effect, and store the
resulting image.
.Pp
.\" ###### Arguments ########################################################
.Sh ARGUMENTS
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It input_filename
The input image. Any format support by GraphicsMagick can be used. The format will be detected automatically.
.It output_filename
The name for the output image to be written. Any format support by GraphicsMagick can be used. The format will be detected by the provided file name extension (e.g. .jpeg, .png, .webp, .pdf, ...). An existing output file will be overwritten.
.It Fl d Ar depth | Fl Fl depth Ar depth
Sets the depth for the "Clothify" effect.
.It Fl w | Fl Fl verbose
Verbose mode: print selected delay and wake-up.
.It Fl h | Fl Fl help
Prints command-line parameters.
.El
.\" ###### Examples #########################################################
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Make-Clothify Bergen.jpeg Bergen-Clothify.jpeg
.It Make-Clothify Bergen.jpeg Bergen-Clothify-with-Border8.jpeg --depth 8 --verbose
.It Make-Clothify Bergen.jpeg Bergen-Clothify-with-Depth5.jpeg -d 5
.El
